2019\n| ''[[3Below: Tales of Arcadia]]''\n| King Fialkov (voice)\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Modern Love (TV series)|Modern Love]]''\n| Michael\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n|2020\n|''Rebel''<ref name=\"drama\">{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/03/10/andy-garcia-rebel-abc-pilot-erin-brockovich/|title=Andy Garcia Joins Katey Sagal in ABC's Erin Brockovich-Inspired Pilot ''Rebel'', From ''Grey'' 's EP Krista Vernoff|work=TVLine.com|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|Julian Cruz\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===Academy Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!| Year\n!| Nominated work\n!| Category\n!| Result\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[The Godfather Part III]]''\n|[[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n===Golden Globes===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!| Year\n!| Nominated work\n!| Category\n!| Result\n|-\n|1991\n|''The Godfather Part III''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n|rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[For Love or Country: The Arturo Sandoval Story|For Love of Country: The Arturo Sandoval Story]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film|Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]]\n|}\n\n===Primetime Emmy Award===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!| Year\n!| Nominated work\n!| Category\n!| Result\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2001\n|rowspan=2|''For Love or Country: The Arturo Sandoval Story''\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Movie|Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Movie]]\n|rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Television Movie|Television Movie]]\n|}\n\n===Miscellaneous awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!| Year\n!| Award\n!| Nominated work\n!| Category\n!| Result\n|-\n|1986\n| New York Film Critics Circle Awards\n|''[[8 Million Ways to Die]]''\n|rowspan=2|Best Supporting Actor\n|rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|1991\n|[[Chicago Film Critics Association Awards]]\n|''The Godfather Part III''\n|-\n| 1997\n| Nostros Golden Eagle Awards\n|\n| Outstanding Performer in Film\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1998\n|rowspan=4|[[ALMA Award]]\n|''Night Falls on Manhattan''\n|Outstanding Actor in a Feature Film\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|''Desperate Measures''\n|Outstanding Actor in a Feature Film in a Crossover Role\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|2000\n|''Just the Ticket''\n|Outstanding Actor in a Feature Film\n|rowspan=3 {{nom}}\n|-\n|2001\n|''1st Annual Latin Grammy Awards''\n| Outstanding Host of a Variety or Awards Special\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2002\n|Phoenix Film Critics Society Awards\n|rowspan=2|''[[Ocean's Eleven]]''\n|Best Acting Ensemble\n|-\n|ALMA Award\n| Outstanding Supporting Actor\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|2005\n|[[Broadcast Film Critics Association Award]]\n|''[[Ocean's Twelve]]''\n|Best Acting Ensemble\n|rowspan=2 {{nom}}\n|-\n|2007\n|ALMA Award\n|''[[The Lost City (2005 film)|The Lost City]]''\n|Best Director\n|-\n|2013\n|[[Boston Film Festival]]\n|''[[At Middleton]]''\n|Best Actor\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|2015\n|[[Annie Award]]\n|''[[Rio 2]]''\n|Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Other honors==\n* 1995: Received a Star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]]\n* 2002: [[Desert Palm Achievement Award]] at the [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]]\n* 2006: Received the Anthony Quinn Award for Achievement in Motion Pictures from [[ALMA Award|The American Latino Media Arts Award]]\n* 2019: [[Medalla de Oro al M\u00e9rito en las Bellas Artes]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.diariolasamericas.com/cultura/andy-garcia-recibe-medalla-oro-al-merito-las-bellas-artes-del-gobierno-espanol-n4139953 |title=Andy Garc\u00eda recibe Medalla de Oro al M\u00e9rito en las Bellas Artes del Gobierno espa\u00f1ol |date=23 December 2017 |access-date=18 February 2019 |newspaper=[[Diario Las Am\u00e9ricas]] |language=es}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books|Andy Garc\u00eda}}\n* [[List of people from Miami]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links and further reading==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{commons|Andy Garc\u00eda}}\n* {{IMDb name|0000412}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.financefoodie.com/2010/03/city-island-diet-w-andy-garcia.html|title= Andy Garcia interview on his City Island diet|website=Finance Foodie|date=March 2010}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.moviehole.net/interviews/20061222_interview_andy_garcia.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070111014437/http://www.moviehole.net/interviews/20061222_interview_andy_garcia.html |archivedate=2007-01-11 |title=Andy Garcia interview for Smokin' Aces|website=MovieHole.net}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.independentfilm.com/festivals/videogalleryfest/andy-garcia-lost-city-miami-film-festival.shtml |title=VIDEO: Andy Garcia at the Miami Film Festival and his new independent film 'Lost City' (Andy speaks to independentfilm.com about his new film set in 1950's Cuba. The film had an emotional screening at the 2006 Miami International Film Festival. (TRT 5min, 9MB)|author= Boutilier, Corey (Executive Director}|website= IndependentFilm.com|date= March 21, 2006}}\n* {{cite news|url=http://flanderstoday.eu/content/face-flanders-%E2%80%94-andy-garcia|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124120224/http://flanderstoday.eu/content/face-flanders-%E2%80%94-andy-garcia|archivedate=2010-11-24|author=Bradshaw, Lisa |title=Andy Garcia \u2013 Film star returns to Ghent after 22 years: 'I've come full circle'|work= Flanders Today}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://blogs.hoycinema.com/movieland/tags/cristiada|title= Photos \"Cristiada\": Andy Garc\u00eda filming in Durango, M\u00e9xico|website=HoyCinema.com Blogs}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia, Andy}}\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American anti-communists]]\n[[Category:American entertainers of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[