itle=Arkansas State Red Wolves vs. Western Kentucky Hilltoppers Box Score|publisher=ESPN.com|accessdate=April 23, 2010}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n==Coaching change==\nOn November 9, 2009, David Elson was officially released as WKU's head coach.  He remained as head coach until the end of the 2009 season. He was replaced by [[Stanford Cardinal football|Stanford]]'s running backs coach [[Willie Taggart]], a Western Kentucky University alumnus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5hUNtrL9bDdlOFMTZRNrNoq8q7MtwD9C5DJ403|title=WKU Hires Stanford's Taggart as Coach|date=November 23, 2009|last=Graves|first=Will|publisher=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football navbox}}\n\n[[Category:2009 Sun Belt Conference football season|WKU]]\n[[Category:Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football seasons]]\n[[Category:College football winless seasons]]\n[[Category:2009 in sports in Kentucky|WKU Football]]\n\n{{collegefootball-2000s-season-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season|sport=football\n  |year=2009\n  |team= WKU Hilltoppers\n  |image=WKU Hilltoppers wordmark.png\n  |image_size=150\n  |conference=Sun Belt Conference\n  |short_conf=SBC\n  |division=\n  |CoachRank=\n  |APRank=\n  |BCSRank=\n  |record=0&ndash;12\n  |conf_record=0&ndash;8\n  |head_coach=[[David Elson]]\n  |off_coach=Walter Wells\n  |def_coach=Mike Dietzel\n  |off_scheme=\n  |def_scheme=\n  |stadium=[[Houchens Industries\u2013L. T. Smith Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 22,113)\n  |champion=\n  |bowl=\n  |bowl_result=\n}}\n{{2009 Sun Belt football standings}}\nThe '''2009 WKU Hilltoppers football team''' represented [[Western Kentucky University]] (WKU) during the [[2009 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The team's head coach was [[David Elson]]. WKU was an [[NCAA Division I FBS independent schools|NCAA Division I FBS independent]] team in 2008, before their move to the [[Su